equestId\":\"req_011CYyA4H8nKQfEgK2LRFsjq\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"16fb5302-9cae-4dd6-a42d-f869b6479521\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T12:06:18.093Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9191cbda-fdd5-41ea-8c6a-d8e7fa6d3b23\",\"version\":\"2.1.74\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/add-support-for-different-remote-for-checkpoints\",\"slug\":\"woolly-exploring-pond\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"16fb5302-9cae-4dd6-a42d-f869b6479521\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"promptId\":\"5f019439-b9dc-471b-9605-0e8e663f0013\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_013mqz6UfoK2c3kJ7yB3ZCT9\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go:25\\nBody: ### Trails push incorrectly blocked by pushDisabled check\\n\\n**High Severity**\\n\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\nThe early return when `ps.pushDisabled` is true now prevents trails from being pushed, but the old code intentionally pushed trails regardless of the `push_sessions` setting. The still-existing `PushTrailsBranch` function documents this: \\\"Trails are always pushed regardless of the push_sessions setting.\\\" Previously, only checkpoints were gated by `isPushSessionsDisabled` inside `pushSessionsBranchCommon`, while `PushTrailsBranch` was called unconditionally. The refactoring places both pushes behind the same `pushDisabled` gate, breaking the trails-always-push invariant.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: 8a46c818-270e-4e8f-a218-a526e122baaa -->\\n\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go#L22-L25\\ncmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go#L209-L214\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<details>\\n<summary>Additional Locations (1)</summary>\\n\\n- [`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go#L209-L214`](https://github.com/entireio/cli/blob/d7ce1c65f66667a6afbd89aff2a75a8727b3fd8b/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go#L209-L214)\\n\\n</details>\\n\\n<div><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/agents?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Web\\\" width=\\\"99\\\" height=\\\"28\\\" src=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-web-dark.png\\\"></picture></a></div>\\n\\n\\nCreated: 2026-03-10T17:52:15Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/versioncheck/versioncheck_test.go:280\\nBody: `errors.New(...)` is used here but the test file does not import the standard library `errors` package, so this won't compile. Add `errors` to the import list (or revert to `fmt.Errorf`).\\nCreated: 2026-03-10T17:53:59Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go:26\\nBody: `push_sessions: false` now short-circuits the entire PrePush, so it also stops pushing `entire/trails/v1`. Previously trails pushing was not gated by `push_sessions` (see `PushTrailsBranch` comment in `push_common.go`). Please confirm the intended behavior; if trails should still push, only gate the checkpoints branch (or introduce a separate setting).\\nCreated: 2026-03-10T17:53:59Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go:102\\nBody: `validateRemoteURL` rejects backslashes. That makes Windows local-path remotes like `C:\\\\path\\\\repo.git` invalid even though local paths are otherwise allowed (tests include `/tmp/repo.git`). Consider allowing `\\\\` (or only rejecting characters that matter for git parsing), or document that Windows paths must use forward slashes.\\n```suggestion\\n\\t// Allow backslashes so Windows local paths like C:\\\\path\\\\repo.git work,\\n\\t// while still rejecting obviously problematic characters.\\n\\tif strings.ContainsAny(url, \\\";|&$`\\\") {\\n```\\nCreated: 2026-03-10T17:53:59Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go:76\\nBody: These warnings log the full checkpoint remote URL from settings. HTTPS remotes can embed credentials/tokens, which would then be written to `.entire/logs/`. Consider redacting userinfo/query parts (or logging only the remote name / host) to avoid leaking secrets.\\nCreated: 2026-03-10T17:54:00Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go:310\\nBody: The docstring says fetch failures are returned to the caller, but the implementation returns `nil` on `git fetch` errors and when the remote ref isn't found. As a result, the warning in `resolvePushSettings` for \\\"failed to fetch branch\\\" will never fire. Either return an error (and let the caller decide to log/ignore) or update the comment + caller logic to match the current non-fatal, no-error behavior.\\n```suggestion\\n\\t\\t// Return error so caller can decide whether this is fatal or can be ignored.\\n\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to fetch branch %s from remote %s: %w\\\", branchName, remote, err)\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Fetch succeeded - create local branch from the remote ref\\n\\tremoteRefName := plumbing.NewRemoteReferenceName(remote, branchName)\\n\\tremoteRef, err := repo.Reference(remoteRefName, true)\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\t// Fetch succeeded but remote ref not found - branch may not exist on remote.\\n\\t\\t// Return error so caller can handle this case appropriately.\\n\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"remote branch %s/%s not found after fetch: %w\\\", remote, branchName, err)\\n```\\nCreated: 2026-03-10T17:54:00Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common.go:94\\nBody: This hint says the checkpoint remote is configured in `.entire/settings.json`, but `settings.Load()` also merges `.entire/settings.local.json`. If a user configures `checkpoint_remote` locally, this message will be misleading; consider wording it as “in settings” or referencing both files.\\n```suggestion\\n\\tfmt.Fprintln(os.Stderr, \\\"[entire] A checkpoint remote is configured in Entire settings (e.g., .entire/settings.json or .entire/settings.local.json) but could not be reached.\\\")\\n```\\nCreated: 2026-03-10T17:54:00Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go:76\\nBody: +1, we need to clean creds from the URL when present.\\nCreated: 2026-03-11T11:09:32Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go:130\\nBody: This could blindside users. If a power user changes that remote URL, rewriting it may be an issue - maybe we warn the user.\\n\\nInstead of overwriting, can't we just create it if it doesn't exist?\\nCreated: 2026-03-11T11:15:04Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go:76\\nBody: added\\nCreated: 2026-03-11T22:23:17Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: README.md:265\\nBody: This \\\"Checkpoint Remote\\\" section still describes configuring `checkpoint_remote` as a full git URL string and says Entire will create a named remote (`entire-checkpoints`). In this PR's implementation, `checkpoint_remote` is a structured `{provider, repo}` object and pushes/fetches use the derived URL directly (no named remote). Please update this section to match the current behavior/design decisions.\\nCreated: 2026-03-12T09:45:34Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/push_common_test.go:56\\nBody: The subtests call t.Parallel() while sharing the same `repo` instance and mutating its references (e.g., setting a remote-tracking ref). This can cause data races and order-dependent/flaky assertions (the \\\"no remote tracking ref exists\\\" case may run after another subtest has created the ref). Remove t.Parallel() from these subtests or create an isolated repo per subtest.\\nCreated: 2026-03-12T09:45:35Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: cmd/entire/cli/strategy/checkpoint_remote.go:132\\nBody: This fetch loop pulls both `entire/checkpoints/v1` and `entire/trails/v1` from the checkpoint URL. In `ManualCommitStrategy.PrePush`, trails are explicitly pushed to the user's push remote (`ps.remote`), so fetching trails from the checkpoint repo can populate the local trails branch with checkpoint-remote history and then push that history to the user's remote. Consider fetching only the checkpoint/metadata branch here (or change the rest of the strategy so trails also consistently use the checkpoint remote).\\nCreated: 2026-03-12T09:45:35Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: README.md:180\\nBody: The README documents `--checkpoint-remote <url>` as taking a full SSH/HTTPS URL, but `entire enable --checkpoint-remote` actually expects `provider:owner/repo` (see flag help in `setup.go`). Please update the flag docs/examples here to match the implemented format.\\nCreated: 2026-03-12T09:45:35Z\\n\\n---\\nFile: README.md:226\\nBody: The configuration table describes `strategy_options.checkpoint_remote` as a Git URL string, but the code reads a structured object (`{\\\"provider\\\":\\\"github\\\",\\\"repo\\\":\\\"org/repo\\\"}`) via `GetCheckpointRemote()` and explicitly ignores legacy string configs. The docs should reflect the structured format so users can configure it correctly.\\n```suggestion\\n| Option                                | Values                           | Description                                                                                             |\\n| ------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| `enabled`                             | `true`, `false` 